# agent86 — Cursor rules
Token efficiency — rtk:
  - rtk is installed for Cursor: `~/.cursor/hooks.json` uses **preToolUse** (matcher `Shell`) to rewrite agent shell commands; `beforeShellExecution` cannot replace commands in Cursor (allow/deny only).
  - Integrated terminal: `~/.cursor/rtk-terminal-auto.zsh` is sourced from `~/.zshrc` and aliases common tools when `TERM_PROGRAM=vscode` (use `/bin/ls`, `command git`, etc. to bypass).
  - `RTK_HOOK_AUDIT=1` is set for integrated terminals via Cursor **User** `settings.json` (`terminal.integrated.env.osx`); audit log: `~/.local/share/rtk/hook-audit.log`.
  - Prefer rtk-wrapped commands for all terminal output that feeds back into context:
      git status / diff / log / add / commit / push  →  rtk git ...
      cat / head / tail <file>                        →  rtk read <file>
      ls / tree                                       →  rtk ls
      grep / rg <pattern>                             →  rtk grep <pattern>
      tsc                                             →  rtk tsc
      pnpm --filter <pkg> test (vitest)               →  rtk vitest run (inside package)
      pnpm -r run build (build output)                →  rtk err pnpm -r run build
  - The hook rewrites automatically for git/cat/ls/grep; explicit rtk prefix needed for
    tsc, vitest, and build error filtering
  - Do not wrap interactive commands or commands whose full output is needed for debugging

## Before starting any task

1. Read **`AGENTS.md`** at the repo root.
2. Read **`docs/superpowers/plans/2026-04-12-agent-ir-v0-implementation.md`** before executing a task step.

## Execution discipline

- Execute **one implementation-plan task at a time**. When that task is complete, **stop, summarize**, then proceed to the next task only when directed or when continuing in the same session with explicit agreement.
- **Commit after each completed task**, not after each individual step within a task.

## Spec and decisions

- **Never edit** `docs/superpowers/specs/2026-04-12-agent-ir-and-ai-language-design.md`. If a spec amendment is needed, add a **PROPOSED** entry to **`docs/impl/spec-proposals.md`** with timestamp, proposing agent, change (diff or clearly marked block), and rationale.
- Put **implementation decisions** in **`docs/impl/v0-decisions.md`**, not in the locked spec and not as a substitute in random inline comments.

## Technical constraints (v0)

- **`grammar_digest`:** Never define or compute it from the **npm version string alone**. Follow **Task 2** in the plan: SHA-256 of the pinned **WASM or `parser.c`** artifact, with a **checked-in constant** and `v0-decisions.md` gate.
- **Snapshot IDs:** Must be **deterministic** — no reliance on `Map` iteration order, no timestamp or random seed in snapshot hashes.
- **Op batches:** Default **atomicity** — never **partial-apply** an op batch unless the batch **explicitly opts in** to partial apply (per spec/plan).
- **`ValidationReport` / errors:** Always use **normative rejection codes** from spec **§12.1** (and `lang.*` rules per spec); **never** prose-only failures for programmatic outcomes.

## Claude (external reviewer)

When a task produces artifacts **suitable for Claude stress-test** (e.g. end of Tasks 0–4 per plan), **state that explicitly** in the summary so a human can paste into claude.ai and relay results back.
